on't get distracted. } (15... a4 16. dxe5 Bxe5 17. Nxe5 Nxe5 18. f4 Ng6 19. e5 Nh7 20. Qd4 Re8 21. Ba3) 16. c4 { [%eval 3.52] } 16... a4 { [%eval 4.04] } 17. Bb2?! { [%eval 2.91] } { Inaccuracy. c5 was best. } { What are you scheming up $2 } (17. c5 Be7 18. d5 Bxc5 19. dxc6 Ng4 20. Be3 Nxe3 21. Nxe3 d6 22. bxa4 Qe8) 17... a3 { [%eval 3.07] } { Let's take a step back and re-evaluate. } 18. Bc1 { [%eval 3.09] } 18... Nxd4 { [%eval 3.72] } { Do you mind if I quickly grab this $2 } 19. N3xd4 { [%eval 3.73] } { You've got sticky fingers. } 19... exd4 { [%eval 3.88] } { I want to thank you for the that thing, with the guy, in the place. I'll never forget it. } 20. e5 { [%eval 3.52] } { Is there anything wrong with robbing the biggest chess app of all time $2 } 20... Bc5 { [%eval 4.03] } 21. exf6 { [%eval 3.68] } { I see. } 21... Qxf6 { [%eval 3.5] } { Sometimes you need to lose a few pawns to accomplish something bigger. } 22. Qd3 { [%eval 3.36] } { Careful with that. It's too much piece for some chess players to handle. } 22... Rbe8?! { [%eval 4.49] } { Inaccuracy. Qg6 was best. } { Careful with that. It's too much piece for some chess players to handle. } (22... Qg6 23. Qh3 Rfe8 24. Bd2 d5 25. cxd5 Re2 26. Rxe2 Bxe2 27. Bd3 Bg4 28. Nh4) (22... d5 23. Nxh6 g6 24. Qh3 Qg7 25. Nxf7+ Kg8 26. Nh6+ Kh8 27. Ng4+ Qh7 28. Bh6) 23. Rxe8 { [%eval 4.04] } { I never liked that rook anyway. He talked too much. } 23... Rxe8 { [%eval 4.63] } { No piece of yours is safe. } 24. Bxh6 { [%eval 4.49] } { Wow $1 Now that's a move. Pat yourself on the back, kid. Brilliant. } 24... Rg8? { [%eval 9.63] } { Mistake. g6 was best. } { Some moves are easy to see. } (24... g6 25. Qh3 Kg8 26. Bg7 Qxg7 27. Nxg7 Kxg7 28. Qxd7 Re7 29. Qd5 Bd6 30. Rd1) 25. Bf4 { [%eval 9.75] } { I didn't plan for this... } 25... Rd8? { [%eval #11] } { Checkmate is now unavoidable. Bf8 was best. } (25... Bf8 26. Qh3+ Qh6 27. Nxh6 gxh6 28. Bxh6 Rxg2+ 29. Kxg2 d3 30. Bxf8+ Kg8 31. Bxd3) 26. Qh3+ { [%eval #10] } { I need to 